{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, if the execution efficiencies are the same, the scores for EX and VES will be identical.",
    "However, if the predicted SQL query executes faster than the ground truth SQL query, the VES value will exceed that of EX.",
    "In practice, each correct predicted SQL query and its ground truth counterpart are executed 100 times, with their run times recorded.",
    "Yet, preliminary experiments indicated that VES could be highly susceptible to fluctuations based on varying hardware, software, and system status.",
    "Hence, for BIRD, EX serves as the stable and dependable metric."
  ]
}